HEADWORD: Gorged
<hw>Gorged</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having a
gorge or throat.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Her.)</fld> <def>Bearing a coronet or ring about
the neck.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Glutted; fed to the full.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gorgelet</ent>⟦br⟧
